  "interpretation_one_liner": "B/A = Om/OL = 0.46 IS the background-null closure; r* lands at rho_m=Om*rho_crit_0 i.e. cosmic mean -> in NFW+2halo this is at the 2-halo floor (asymptotic), not a discrete radius. Without the 2-halo floor the crossing sits in the outskirt band; with the floor included the closure case becomes degenerate. Honest answer: Om/OL is not derived, it is *imposed* by demanding <sigma_eff>=0 on the cosmic mean, which trivialises the cluster crossover."
